A MAN has been reported to the Procurator Fiscal following a trespass incident which brought trains to a standstill.&nbsp;The 47-year-old was found on the line at around 2.15pm yesterday at Cowlairs junction, near Springburn.A train was approaching and he is believed to have suffered minor injuries after being struck.The incident caused disruption to services including trains from Glasgow Queen Street to Bishopbriggs.A spokesman for British Transport Police said: &quot;A man was charged and released pending a report to the Procurator Fiscal.&quot;